pyPheWAS.pyPhewas – pyPhewas file¶

Phewas object used to run different phenotype statistical anaylses.

This module is used to execute a variety of different analyses on large sets of patient phenotype data.

class pyPheWAS.pyPhewas.Phewas(inputfile, groupfile, path='', covariates='genotype', save='', output='')[source]¶

The Phewas object is used to run different types of Phewas regressions and plots.

__init__(inputfile, groupfile, path='', covariates='genotype', save='', output='')[source]¶

Creates a Phewas object with the given parameters.

Parameters:
  • inputfile – the name of the phenotype file (no path)
  • groupfile – the name of the genotype file (no path)
  • path – the path to the inputfile and groupfile, this path will be used for all outputs as well. Defaults to empty path (i.e. current directory)
  • covariates – the covariates that want to be run by pyPhewas, each additional covariate must be delimited by a + sign (i.e ‘genotype+age’)
  • save – the filename to save the generated plot. The default is an empty string. This will result in the plot being displayed.
  • output – the filename to save the regression data. The default is an empty string.
replot()[source]¶

Replots the regression that was executed.

run_lin()[source]¶

Runs a linear regression on the current arguments.

Upon completion, the results of the regression are saved by the object so that they can be used without creating a new regression.

run_log()[source]¶

Runs a logarithmic regression on the current arguments.

Upon completion, the results of the regression are saved by the object so that they can be used without creating a new regression.

pyPheWAS.pyPhewaslog – pyPhewaslog file¶

Python implemented code for running logarithmic regressions on PheWAS inputs.

Calculates the odds and p-value for using a logarithmic regression.

pyPheWAS.pyPhewaslog.generate_feature_matrix(genotypes, phenotypes)[source]¶

Generate the feature matrix from the genotype and phenotype matrix.

The feature matrix is used to calculate the regressions. The feature matrix has a vector for each ID, each vector has the 0/1 count as for whether or not rhat phewas code showed up for the given patient ID.
